problem.text:
Let \(P\) be a finite poset with a bottom element \(0\). Show that if \(x\) covers exactly one element of \(P\), then
\[
\mu(x,0)=
\begin{cases}
-1 & \text{if }x\text{ covers }0,\\
0 & \text{otherwise.}
\end{cases}
\]
For any \(n\in\mathbb{Z}\), construct a poset containing an element \(x\) with \(\mu(x)=n\).
